# Operational technology layers (hook)

**Canonical doc:** [docs/Z_OPERATIONAL_TECHNOLOGY_LAYERS.md](docs/Z_OPERATIONAL_TECHNOLOGY_LAYERS.md)

## One-line law

```text
Use layered tools — NOT as the soul of the ecosystem.
```

## Layer roles (summary)

| Layer | Role |
| ----- | ---- |
| Cursor | Builder companion — Turtle branches, docs-first, PRs; no auto-deploy |
| GitHub | Vault + review + history — human merge on `main` |
| Cloudflare | Optional future edge — minimal now; see Cloudflare precautions doc |
| Z-DAIO | Governance / continuity / orchestration **posture** |
| Z-ADTF | Federation continuity **observatory** — not control plane |

## Sealed with ADTF

```text
federation ≠ authority
topology ≠ ownership
```

## When building

- Prefer linking existing governance docs over inventing parallel policy.
- Defer Cloudflare production, public NAS, and exposed RDP until chartered and human-gated.
- Complete real-world Z-ADTF validation loop before federation mock UI expansion.

Full stack doctrine, phased Cloudflare table, and Mauritius learning gate: **Z_OPERATIONAL_TECHNOLOGY_LAYERS.md**.
